1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Did you know Earth is closest to the Sun in January?

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:07,200
So why are we freezing in winter?

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,600
It's all about axial tilt—not distance.

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,400
Earth's axis is tilted at 23.5 degrees.

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:18,000
This tilt causes different parts of Earth to receive varying sunlight throughout the year.

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,800
In summer, the Northern Hemisphere tilts toward the Sun, heating things up!

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:28,800
So, the next time you enjoy the sun, remember—it’s not about how close we are.

8
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,200
Follow for more mind-blowing science facts!
